50|$|Given its {{excellent}} <b>optical</b> <b>qualities,</b> {{the telescope}} {{has been used}} primarily for imaging and photometric work, in which it regularly outperforms much larger telescopes located elsewhere. Among {{the results from this}} telescope have been the discovery of MACHOs in the Andromeda Galaxy; the validation of the Stromvil photometric filter system; evidence for how the shape and dimensions of galaxies have changed over the age of the universe; discovery of the first binary 'Vesta chip' asteroid; and the characterization and classification by visible colors of some 100 Trans-Neptunian objects, most of them fainter than magnitude 21.|$|E
